@node Backup_Gadget
    Name:  Backup Gadget

 Purpose:  This Gadget is used to start the Backup process.

 Warning:  Make sure the Backup Configuration is set up correctly.

Keyboard:  "B"
@endnode

@node Restore_Gadget
    Name:  Restore Gadget

 Purpose:  This Gadget is used to start the Restore process.

 Warning:  Make sure the Restore Configuration is set up correctly.

Keyboard:  "R"
@endnode

@node Scheduler_Gadget
    Name:  Scheduler Gadget

 Purpose:  This Gadget is used to select the Ami-Back Scheduler
              Configuration.

 Warning:  Ami-Sched MUST be running for the scheduler events to
              occur.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node Quit_Gadget
    Name:  Quit Gadget

 Purpose:  This Gadget is used to Quit Ami-Back.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "Q"
@endnode

@node MENU_NEWCONFIG
    Name:  New Configuration (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  To create a new Ami-Back configuration.

 Warning:  Will assume the defaults of the current configuration.

Keyboard:  Right-Amiga "N"
@endnode

@node MENU_LOADCONFIG
    Name:  Load Configuration (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  To load a different Ami-Back configuration file.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  Right-Amiga "L"
@endnode

@node MENU_SAVECONFIG
    Name:  Save Configuration (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  To save the current Ami-Back configuration file.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  Right-Amiga "S"
@endnode

@node MENU_SNAPSHOT
    Name:  SnapShot (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  When using a Workbench screen you can save the Ami-Back window
           anywhere on the current screen.  When Ami-Back is executed it
           will open the window at the saved location.

 Warning:  This ONLY works with the Workbench screen type; it will not
           work with the custom screen.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node MENU_ABOUT
    Name:  About (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  To show information about Moonlighter Software Development, Inc.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node MENU_QUIT
    Name:  Quit (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  To Quit Ami-Back.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  Right-Amiga "Q"
@endnode

@node MENU_EDITBACKUP
    Name:  Backup Configuration (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  Allows Editing Backup Configuration Parameters.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  Right-Amiga "B"
@endnode

@node MENU_EDITRESTORE
    Name:  Restore Configuration (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  Allows Editing Restore Configuration Parameters.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  Right-Amiga "R"
@endnode

@node MENU_EDITPROG
    Name:  Program Configuration (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  Allows Editing Program Configuration Parameters.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  Right-Amiga "P"
@endnode

@node MENU_WORKBENCHTYPE
    Name:  Workbench (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  Change current screen type to a Workbench screen.

 Warning:  Will have no effect if current screen is a Workbench screen.

Keyboard:  Right-Amiga "W"
@endnode

@node MENU_CUSTOMTYPE
    Name:  Custom (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  Change current screen to custom 640 x 200 screen.

 Warning:  Will have no effect if current screen is a Workbench screen.

Keyboard:  Right-Amiga "C"
@endnode

@node MENU_TAPEERASE
    Name:  Erase (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  To ERASE data from tape.

 Warning:  Only active if Backup Configuration destination device is
           "Tape Drive."

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node MENU_TAPEREWIND
    Name:  Rewind (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  Will REWIND tape to beginning.

 Warning:  Only active if Backup Configuration destination device is
           "Tape Drive."

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node MENU_TAPERETENSION
    Name:  Retension (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  To retension tape.

 Warning:  Only active if Backup Configuration destination device is
           "Tape Drive."

           Should be done with NEW tapes or tapes that haven't been used for
           long periods of time.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node MENU_TAPEFORMAT
    Name:  Format (Menu Item)

 Purpose:  Will FORMAT a tape.

 Warning:  Only active if Backup Configuration destination device is
           "Tape Drive."

           This option will ONLY work with DIRECT ACCESSING tape drives.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_SAVE
    Name:  Save Gadget

 Purpose:  Will save ALL current Backup Configuration settings.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_USE
    Name:  Use Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows using current Backup Configuration settings.

 Warning:  Does NOT save settings to configuration file.  Current settings
           will be lost at termination of program.

Keyboard:  "U"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_CANCEL
    Name:  Cancel Gadget

 Purpose:  To cancel Backup Configuration.

 Warning:  Backup Configuration settings will be RESET back to LOAD settings.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_SOURCE
    Name:  Source Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows MANUAL entry for backup source device.  For multiple
           devices, separate the device/directory names with a SPACE.

           This can be either a device or a directory name.  This is
           dependent upon the backup type.

           Selecting the Icons above the gadget will automatically append
           the corresponding name to the backup source.

 Warning:  You MUST press RETURN after making your selections or Ami-Back
           WILL NOT recognize the entered devices.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_DEST
    Name:  Destination Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selecting a backup destination device.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "D"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_SUBDIR
    Name:  Include Sub-Dirs Gadget

 Purpose:  Will cause Ami-Back to search sub-directories of source device.
           If selected it will include ALL subdirectories.  If not, it will
           only include files in the device root directory.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "I"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_TYPE
    Name:  Backup Type Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selecting the Backup Type.

           1) Complete - Will backup ALL files on source device(s).

           2) Selective - Will allow you to selectively backup
              files and/or directories to backup device(s).

           3) 911-Recovery - Will attempt to recover and backup directories
              and/or files on a crashed partition (hard drive.)  This
              partition must be a FFS, and it must be mounted.

           4) Image - This will do an image backup of a device(s).  This is
              a good way to backup NON-AmigaDOS file systems.  It is NOT
              however recommended for AmigaDOS file system backups due to
              the limited restore capabilities of this type of backup.

 Warning:  1) 911-Recovery Mode will only Backup ONE device, and it
              must use FFS.

           2) You will NOT be able to perform a selective restore of an
              Image backup.

           Image will ONLY backup device(s).

Keyboard:  "B"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_COMPRESSION
    Name:  Compression Gadget

 Purpose:  When selected Ami-Back will compress data during backup.

 Warning:  This could increase backup time in some cases, especially to
           devices other than floppies.

Keyboard:  "P"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_VERIFYMODE
    Name:  Verify Mode Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selecting backup verify type.

           1) Off - No compression.

           2) Standard - Ami-Back will re-read data off destination device
              and check it against data in buffer.

           3) Compare - Ami-Back will perform a compare restore after the
              backup is complete.  See "Compare Restore" for more
              information.

 Warning:  If you do not use some kind of verify option there is NO WAY to
           guarantee data intregrety during backup.  There are however some
           devices that are READ-AFTER-WRITE, i.e., Tape Drives.

Keyboard:  "V"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_SETARCHIVEBIT
    Name:  Set Archive Bit Gadget

 Purpose:  Will cause Ami-Back to set the file archive bit after the file
           has been backed up.

 Warning:  Not setting this option prevents performing incremental backups
           done with archive bit.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_LABELSET
    Name:  Label Backup Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows entering an 80 column description to be stored with the
           backup index.  This will allow you to label your backups and
           retain this information with your backup.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "K"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_USEFILTER
    Name:  Use Backup Filter Gadget

 Purpose:  If selected Ami-Back will use the backup filter parameters during
           the search of the source device.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "F"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_CONFIGFILTER
    Name:  Configure Filter Gadget

 Purpose:  Will bring up Backup Filter and allow changing parameters.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "L"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_PASSWDPROT
    Name:  Password Protect Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows the entering of a password to protect backup data.

 Warning:  You must know the password to restore a backup protected with
           a password.  If the password is forgotten there is NO WAY to
           recover the lost data.

Keyboard:  "T"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_WRITENOTIFY
    Name:  Write Notify Gadget

 Purpose:  If selected Ami-Back will notify you if ANY type of data is on
           destination device prior to writing to it.

 Warning:  This will occur for EACH change of backup media.

Keyboard:  "W"
@endnode

@node GAD_BU_CATALOG
    Name:  Backup Catalog Gadget

 Purpose:  If selected Ami-Back will produce a requester at end of a backup
           allowing you to save a catalog (tree listing) of the backup.  It
           will display directories, sub-directories, and files (with size).

           You may save this to an AmigaDOS or PRT: device.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "G"
@endnode

@node GAD_CLR
    Name:  CLR Gadget

 Purpose:  To clear out Backup Source or Restore Destination Gadgets.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_CONFIGTAPE
    Name:  Configure Tape

 Purpose:  Brings up Tape Configuration allowing you to change Tape Drive
           configuration parameters.

 Warning:  Will ONLY be displayed if Backup Destination or Restore Source
           Gadget selected is "Tape Drive."

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_FILENAME
    Name:  File Name Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows entering filename and path of Backup Destination or
           Restore Source device when using AmigaDOS File option.

           If backing up to another hard drive partition this would be the
           preferred method.  This would allow you to maintain the
           destination device as a AmigaDOS device.

           default: RAM:Ami-Back.bac

 Warning:  There MUST be enough room on destination device to store the file.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_SAVE
    Name:  Save Gadget

 Purpose:  Will save ALL current Restore Configuration settings.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_USE
    Name:  Use Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows using current Restore Configuration settings.

 Warning:  Does NOT save settings to configuration file.  Current settings
           will be lost at termination of program.

Keyboard:  "U"
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_CANCEL
    Name:  Cancel Gadget

 Purpose:  To cancel Restore Configuration.

 Warning:  Restore Configuration settings will be RESET to LOAD settings.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_DEST
    Name:  Destination Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows MANUAL entry for restore source device.  For multiple
           devices separate the device/directory names with a SPACE.

           This can be either a device or a directory name.  This is
           dependent upon the restore type.

           Selecting the Icons above the gadget will automatically append
           the corresponding device name to the restore destination.

 Warning:  You MUST press RETURN after entry or Ami-Back WILL NOT
           recognize your selection.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_SOURCE
    Name:  Source Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selecting Restore source device.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "O"
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_TYPE
    Name:  Restore Type Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selecting the Restore Type.

           1) Complete - Will restore ALL files to destination device(s).

           2) Selective - Will allow you to selectively restore
              files and/or directories to the destination device(s).

           3) Compare - Will perform a compare of files on the source
              device to files on the destination device.  An actual file
              transfer will NOT occur.

           4) Image - This will do an image restore to a device(s).  If you
              backed up more than one device using the Image type, you can
              restore only one of those devices by using NIL: or NULL: as
              as destination device.

 Warning:  1) 911-Recovery Mode will only Backup ONE device, and must use
              FFS.

           2) You will NOT be able to perform a selective restore of an
              Image backup.

           3) On Image restores the destination device MUST be the same size
              (number of blocks) as the device backed up.

Keyboard:  "R"
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_DIRSTRUCT
    Name:  Dir Structure Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows restoring files from a backup to a SINGLE directory or
           will maintain the directory structure of the backup.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "I"
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_FILEPROBIT
    Name:  File Protection Bits Gadget

 Purpose:  If selected will enable "Pro Bits" gadgets and allow you set
           file protection bits during restoration.
 Warning:  Using this will effect ALL files during restoration.

Keyboard:  "P"
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_FILEDATE
    Name:  File Date Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows you to select file date used during restoration.  Either
           file date stored on backup, or current system date.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "F"
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_DUPFILEDET
    Name:  File Detection Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows control of file detection during restoration.  If file
           already exist you have the following options:

           1)  Write-Over - Will write over file if exist.

           2)  Write-Over (Date) - Will write over file if file on hard
               disk (device) is older than file to be restored.

           3)  Skip-Over - If file exist it will NOT be restored.

           4)  Rename - If file exist you will be prompted to rename the file,
               or skip it.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "E"
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_PROBITR
    Name:  Pro Bits "R" Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows setting/not setting the READ protection bit during the
           restoration.  The File Protection Bits Gadget MUST be in
           "User Select" for this option to work.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_PROBITW
    Name:  Pro Bits "W" Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows setting/not setting the WRITE protection bit during the
           restoration.  The File Protection Bits Gadget MUST be in
           "User Select" for this option to work.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_PROBITP
    Name:  Pro Bits "W" Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows setting/not setting the WRITE protection bit during the
           restoration.  The File Protection Bits Gadget MUST be in
           "User Select" for this option to work.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_PROBITE
    Name:  Pro Bits "E" Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows setting/not setting the EXECUTE protection bit during the
           restoration.  The File Protection Bits Gadget MUST be in
           "User Select" for this option to work.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_PROBITA
    Name:  Pro Bits "A" Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows setting/not setting the ARCHIVE protection bit during the
           restoration.  The File Protection Bits Gadget MUST be in
           "User Select" for this option to work.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_PROBITD
    Name:  Pro Bits "D" Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows setting/not setting the DELETE protection bit during the
           restoration.  The File Protection Bits Gadget MUST be in
           "User Select" for this option to work.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_USEFILTER
    Name:  User Restore Filter Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows use of Restore Filter during restoration.

 Warning:  Only applicable during Complete or Compare Restore mode.

Keyboard:  "T"
@endnode

@node GAD_RS_CONFIGFILTER
    Name:  Configure Filter Gadget

 Purpose:  Will bring up Restore Filter and allow changing parameters.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "L"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_DEVICE
    Name:  Device Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows manual entry of SCSI device used for Tape Drive.

 Warning:  1) Some controllers may have more than one device.  See your
              user's manual to determine which to use.

           2) The device name IS case sensitive.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_DEVLEFT
    Name:  Device LEFT Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows searching device list.  Searches in the reverse direction.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_DEVRIGHT
    Name:  Device RIGHT Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows searching device list.  Searches in the forward direction.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

