    Name:  SCSI ID Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows setting SCSI ID number of tape drive.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_UNITLEFT
    Name:  SCSI ID LEFT Gadget

 Purpose:  Decrements SCSI ID number by 1.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_UNITRIGHT
    Name:  SCSI ID RIGHT Gadget

 Purpose:  Increments SCSI ID number by 1.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_TAPESIZE
    Name:  Tape Size Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows specification of tape size in megabytes.

 Warning:  May be selected only if Auto Tape Size is set to NO.

Keyboard:  "z"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_TAPESIZELEFT
    Name:  Tape Size LEFT Gadget

 Purpose:  Decrements tape size by 1 MB.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_TAPESIZERIGHT
    Name:  Tape Size RIGHT Gadget

 Purpose:  Increments tape size by 1 MB.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_AUTOSIZE
    Name:  Auto Tape Size Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows Ami-Back to set tape size.

 Warning:  Set to NO if there are problems backing up to multiple tapes.

Keyboard:  "o"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_DRIVETYPE
    Name:  Drive Type Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selecting between Sequential or Direct Access tape drives.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "p"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_BLOCK
    Name:  Block Size Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows specifying block length for tape drive.

 Warning:  Most SCSI drives use a fixed block length of 512k.

Keyboard:  "B"

@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_BLOCKLEFT
    Name:  Block Size LEFT Gadget

 Purpose:  Decrements Block Size by 1 kilobyte.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_BLOCKRIGHT
    Name:  Block Size RIGHT Gadget

 Purpose:  Increments Block Size by 1 kilobyte.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_NUMBERBLOCKS
    Name:  MaxTransfer (Blocks) Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows specification of maximum number of blocks to be written to
           tape drive.

 Warning:  Changing this value can cause erratic behavior during tape drive
           operation.

Keyboard:  "M"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_NUMBERBLOCKSLEFT
    Name:  MaxTransfer LEFT Gadget

 Purpose:  Decrements number of blocks to be transferred by 1.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_NUMBERBLOCKSRIGHT
    Name:  MaxTransfer RIGHT Gadget

 Purpose:  Increments number of blocks to be transferred by 1.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_BLOCKTYPE
    Name:  Block Type Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows specifying Fixed or Variable Block type.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "T"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_IO
    Name:  I/O Mode Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows specifying Asynchronous or Synchronous mode.

 Warning:  Synchronous mode is slower but may be required with some configs.

Keyboard:  "I"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_BUF
    Name:  BU Buffer (x2) Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selection of buffer size during backup.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "f"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_BUFRS
    Name:  RS Buffer Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selection of buffer size during restore.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "R"
@endnode  

@node GAD_TAPE_APPEND
    Name:  Tape Append Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows addition of new backups to tapes with existing backup
           information.

 Warning:  Overwriting a tape that has multiple backups will destroy all
           the backups on the tape.

Keyboard:  "e"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_AUTORET
    Name:  Auto Retension Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selection of automatically retensioning tapes.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_READCONFIG
    Name:  Read Defaults Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows Ami-Back to read the default settings for tape drive.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_USE
    Name:  Use Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows use of selected parameters.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "U"
@endnode

@node GAD_TAPE_CANCEL
    Name:  Cancel Gadget

 Purpose:  Returns to configuration screen without using current settings.

 Warning:  All selected parameters will be reset to last-used values.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_FILTER_USE
    Name:  Use Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows use of selected configuration.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "U"
@endnode

@node GAD_FILTER_CANCEL
    Name:  Cancel Gadget

 Purpose:  Returns to backup configuration screen without using current
           settings.

 Warning:  All selected parameters will be returned to last saved values.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

