@endnode

@node GAD_BR_CONTINUE
    Name:  Begin Backup Gadget

 Purpose:  Begins execution of backup.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "B"
@endnode

@node GAD_BR_CANCEL
    Name:  Quit Backup Gadget

 Purpose:  Quits backup before beginning.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "Q"
@endnode

@node GAD_BR_ABORT
    Name:  Abort Gadget

 Purpose:  Aborts backup in progress.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "A"
@endnode

@node GAD_BR_LISTVIEW
    Name:  Backup Error List

 Purpose:  Any errors encountered during backup will be listed here.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_BR_EXIST
    Name:  File Exist Gadget

 Purpose:  If selected during a compare restore the existance of the file
           will be check.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_BR_DATA
    Name:  Data Gadget
    
 Purpose:  If selected during a compare restore the data from the backup
           media will be compared against the data on the hard drive.  If
           there is a difference you will be notified.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_BR_TIME
    Name:  Time/Date Stamp Gadget

 Purpose:  If selected during a compare restore the Time/Date stamps are
           compared between the backup media and the hard drive.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_BR_PROTECTION
    Name:  Protection Bits Gadget

 Purpose:  If selected during a compare restore the Protection Bits are
           compared between the backup media and the hard drive.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_BR_COMMENT
    Name:  File Comment Gadget

 Purpose:  If selected during a compare restore the Comments are
           compared between the backup media and the hard drive.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_SELECT_CONTINUE
    Name:  Continue Gadget

 Purpose:  Will continue with selective backup.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "o"
@endnode

@node GAD_SELECT_CANCEL
    Name:  Cancel Gadget

 Purpose:  Will cancel backup from file/dir selection window.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_SELECT_SCROLLER
    Name:  File/Directory Scroll Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows scrolling to file/directories that are not immediately
           visible.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_SELECT_MARK
    Name:  Mark to Exclude/Include Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows specification of inclusion or exclusion of marked files
           and directories.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_SELECT_MARKALL
    Name:  Mark All Gadget

 Purpose:  Will select all files and directories in source device.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "a"
@endnode

@node GAD_SELECT_CLEARALL
    Name:  Clear All Gadget

 Purpose:  Will unselect all files and directories in source device.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "l"
@endnode

@node GAD_SELECT_PARENT
    Name:  Parent Gadget

 Purpose:  Will display the files and directories from the parent of the
           currently specified directory.  Will not go farther back than the
           source directory specified in the backup configuration.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "P"
@endnode

@node GAD_SCHED_CONFIG
    Name:  Scheduler Configuration Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selection from 1 of 10 stored scheduler configurations.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "h"
@endnode

@node GAD_SCHED_NAME
    Name:  Backup Configuration String Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selection of which backup configuration file to use with
           scheduled backup.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_SCHED_ACTIVE
    Name:  Configuration Status Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows specification of whether scheduler is active or inactive.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "f"
@endnode

@node GAD_SCHED_SAVE
    Name:  Save Gadget

 Purpose:  Will save current parameters to selected scheduler configuration,
           and exit scheduler configuration mode.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_SCHED_CANCEL
    Name:  Cancel Gadget

 Purpose:  Will exit scheduler configuration mode without saving currently
           specified parameters.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_SCHED_DEFAULT
    Name:  Default Settings Gadget

 Purpose:  Will reset all scheduler options to the default values.  Backups
           will be scheduled for 12:00 am daily, configuration status will be
           inactive, and Ami-Back.config will be the selected backup
           configuration file.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "D"
@endnode

@node GAD_SCHED_TYPE
    Name:  Event Type Gadget

 Purpose:  Specifies whether the scheduler will perform a backup at the set
           time or simply notify the user that a backup is to be performed.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "E"
@endnode

@node GAD_PRG_SAVE
    Name:  Save Gadget

 Purpose:  Will save current program configuration settings as default.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "S"
@endnode

@node GAD_PRG_CANCEL
    Name:  Cancel Gadget

 Purpose:  Will exit the program configuration mode without saving any of
           the specified parameters.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode

@node GAD_PRG_PROGRAMPATH
    Name:  Ami-Back Program Path String Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows specification of the full program path for Ami-Back.

 Warning:  This path MUST include the program name.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PRG_INDEXPATH
    Name:  Index File Path String Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows specification of the location index files that Ami-Back
           creates.

 Warning:  The name of the file is NOT to be entered here.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PRG_LOGPATH
    Name:  Log File Path String Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows specification of the location for the Ami-Back log file.

 Warning:  The name of the file is NOT to be entered here.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PRG_FILTERPATH
    Name:  Backup Filter Path String Gadget

 Purpose:  The full path of the backup filter file is to be entered here.

 Warning:  This path MUST include the name of the backup filter to be used.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PRG_RSFILTERPATH
    Name:  Restore Filter Path String Gadget

 Purpose:  The full path of the restore filter file is to be entered here.

 Warning:  This path MUST include the name of the restore filter to be used.

Keyboard:  None.
@endnode

@node GAD_PRG_DISPLAYALERT
    Name:  Display Alert Gadget

 Purpose:  This allows the specification of the desired program display
           alert.  Choices are None, Beep Only, Flash Only, and
           Flash and Beep.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "D"
@endnode

@node GAD_PRG_PROGRAMOPS
    Name:  Program Operations Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows selection of Asynchronous or Synchronous mode of program
           operation.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "P"
@endnode

@node GAD_PRG_INDEXLOCATION
    Name:  Index File Location

 Purpose:  Allows specification of location of backup index file.  User may
           select (then location must be given in the Index File Path string
           gadget) or it can be automatically attached to the backup (floppy
           backups only).

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "I"
@endnode

@node GAD_PRG_SHOWCONFIG
    Name:  Show Configuration First Gadget

 Purpose:  Allows specification of whether or not Ami-Back should display
           backup or restore configuration before actually performing the
           backup or restore.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "h"
@endnode

@node GAD_ABOUT_CONTINUE
    Name:  Continue Gadget

 Purpose:  Closes About information window.

 Warning:  None.

Keyboard:  "C"
@endnode
